command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- Example 1 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: PS C:\> $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $url -Method POST -ContentType 'text/xml' -Body $payload -Headers $headers PS C:\> [xml]$functionout = $r.Content PS C:\> Convert-EasitXMLToPsObject -Response $functionout

maml:description.maml:para: Get data from Easit BPS / Easit GO with web services.

Connects to Easit BPS / Easit GO web service with url, apikey and view and returns each item as an objects.
If the view specified to get items from contains two or more fields with the same name, the value from the latest field will be used.
All returning objects will have these properties requestedPage, totalNumberOfPages and totalNumberOfItems beyond the once provided by the importViewIdentifier.

maml:Description.maml:para: URL to Easit BPS / Easit GO web service. Default = http://localhost/webservice/
API-key for Easit BPS / Easit GO.
Order in which to sort data, Descending or Ascending.
Used to get data from specific page in view. Each page contains 25 items.

Used to filter data.
Example: ColumnName,comparator,value
Valid comparator: EQUALS, NOT_EQUALS, IN, NOT_IN, GREATER_THAN, GREATER_THAN_OR_EQUALS, LESS_THAN, LESS_THAN_OR_EQUALS, LIKE, NOT_LIKE

If specified, payload will be save as payload_1.xml (or next available number) to your desktop instead of sent to Easit BPS / Easit GO. This parameter does not append, rewrite or remove any files from your desktop.

Used if system is using SSO with IWA (Active Directory). Not needed when using SSO with SAML2.
Cmdlet will use the credentials of the current user to send the web request.
This parameter is required when Internet Explorer is not installed on the computers, such as on a Server Core installation of a Windows Server operating system.
API-key for Easit BPS / Easit GO.

Used to filter data.
Example: ColumnName,comparator,value
Valid comparator: EQUALS, NOT_EQUALS, IN, NOT_IN, GREATER_THAN, GREATER_THAN_OR_EQUALS, LESS_THAN, LESS_THAN_OR_EQUALS, LIKE, NOT_LIKE

If specified, payload will be save as payload_1.xml (or next available number) to your desktop instead of sent to Easit BPS / Easit GO. This parameter does not append, rewrite or remove any files from your desktop.
Order in which to sort data, Descending or Ascending.

Used if system is using SSO with IWA (Active Directory). Not needed when using SSO with SAML2.
Cmdlet will use the credentials of the current user to send the web request.
URL to Easit BPS / Easit GO web service. Default = http://localhost/webservice/
This parameter is required when Internet Explorer is not installed on the computers, such as on a Server Core installation of a Windows Server operating system.
Used to get data from specific page in view. Each page contains 25 items.

command:example.maml:title: -------------------------- EXAMPLE 3 --------------------------
command:example.dev:code: $getGoItemsParams = @{ url = 'http://localhost/test/webservice/' api = '4745f62b7371c2aa5cb80be8cd56e6372f495f6g8c60494ek7f231548bb2a375' view = 'RequestServiceRequests' ColumnFilter = 'Name,EQUALS,Extern organisation' } Get-GOItems @getGoItemsParams

maml:description.maml:para: "Private" cmdlet that act as helper function.
This cmdlet "builds" a XML-object that can be sent to Easit BPS and Easit GO to get or create/update items.

maml:Description.maml:para: Tells cmdlet that the XML-object should be built in order to get items from Easit BPS or Easit GO.

Used to filter data.
Example: ColumnName,comparator,value
Tells cmdlet what value that the XML-object should set for the ItemViewIdentifier property.
Tells cmdlet what value that the XML-object should set for the Page property.
Tells cmdlet what value that the XML-object should set for the SortColumn property.
Tells cmdlet what value that the XML-object should set as the attribut order for the SortColumn property.
Tells cmdlet that the XML-object should be built in order to import items to Easit BPS or Easit GO.
Tells cmdlet what value that the XML-object should set for the ImportHandlerIdentifier property. As this is an "global" property and not for any specific item it is handled separatly.
The values provided in this parameter will represent the XML properties for the item sent.
